\subtree{
\title{QRI Valence Skill}
\p{The \strong{Symmetry Theory of Valence (STV)} proposes that the valence (pleasantness/unpleasantness) of a conscious state is determined by the symmetry of its mathematical representation. This skill integrates QRI research with computational implementations.}

\subtree{
\title{Core Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Symmetry Theory of Valence (STV)}
\blockquote{"The valence of a moment of consciousness is precisely determined by the symmetry of the mathematical object that describes it." — Michael Edward Johnson, Principia Qualia (2016)}

\p{\strong{Key Claims:}}

\ol{
\li{Consciousness has mathematical structure (qualia formalism)}
\li{Symmetry in that structure correlates with positive valence}
\li{Broken symmetries manifest as suffering/dissonance}
\li{Valence is measurable and optimizable}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{XY Model Topology (smoothbrains.net)}
\p{The phenomenal field behaves like a 2D XY spin model:}

\pre{\startverb
| State | Temperature (τ) | Vortices | Valence | Phenomenology |
|-------|-----------------|----------|---------|---------------|
| Frustrated | τ >> τ* | Many, proliferating | -3 | Scattered, anxious, "buzzing" |
| Disordered | τ > τ* | Some, mobile | -1 to -2 | Unfocused, dissonant |
| Critical (BKT) | τ ≈ τ* | Paired, bound | 0 | Liminal, transitional |
| Ordered | τ < τ* | Few, annihilating | +1 to +2 | Coherent, smooth |
| Resolved | τ << τ* | None | +3 | Deeply peaceful, consonant |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{BKT Transition} (Berezinskii-Kosterlitz-Thouless):}

\ul{
\li{Below τ*: vortex-antivortex pairs bound → low entropy, high symmetry}
\li{Above τ*: vortices proliferate → high entropy, broken symmetry}
\li{At τ*: phase transition where defects can annihilate}
}
}

